BusinessName.BusinessNameLine1Txt: DOUGLAS COUNTY PUBLIC HEALTH SVCS GROUP INC

IRS990.ActivityOrMissionDesc: TO PROVIDE AFFORDABLE, ACCESSIBLE, QUALITY HEALTH CARE TO ALL WITHIN THE SERVICE AREA. SERVICES WILL BE PROVIDED WITHOUT REGARD TO AGE, RACE, CREED, DISABILITY OR STATUS.
IRS990.MissionDesc: IT IS THE MISSION OF THE DOUGLAS COUNTY PUBLIC HEALTH SERVICES GROUP, INC. DBA/MISSOURI OZARKS COMMUNITY HEALTH, TO PROVIDE QUALITY, AFFORDABLE PRIMARY MEDICAL, DENTAL, AND BEHAVIORAL HEALTH CARE TO ALL.
IRS990.Desc: DURING FISCAL YEAR 2018, MISSOURI OZARKS COMMUNITY HEALTH (MOCH) HAD 19,885 MEDICAL ENCOUNTERS (VISITS) THAT PROVIDED QUALITY CARE TO THE RURAL POPULATION OF DOUGLAS, OZARK, WRIGHT, AND TEXAS COUNTIES IN MISSOURI. MOCH STRIVES TO PROVIDE THIS QUALITY CARE THROUGH A VARIETY OF MEDICAL SERVICES THAT INCLUDE, BUT ARE NOT LIMITED TO, ADULT MEDICINE, PEDIATRIC CARE, ADOLESCENT HEALTH, NUTRITIONAL HEALTH, URGENT MEDICAL CARE, LABORATORY AND RADIOLOGY TESTING, AND PHARMACY SERVICES. FOR SERVICES OUTSIDE OF MOCH'S SCOPE AND ABILITY, PATIENTS ARE REFERRED TO ORGANIZATIONS NEAR OUR SERVICE AREA THAT CAN PROVIDE THE QUALITY OF CARE THAT MOCH PATIENTS EXPECT FOR MEDICAL ENCOUNTERS.

ProgSrvcAccomActy2Grp.Desc: MISSOURI OZARKS COMMUNITY HEALTH PROVIDES QUALITY PREVENTATIVE AND RESTORATIVE DENTAL CARE IN DOUGLAS, OZARK, WRIGHT, AND TEXAS COUNTIES IN MISSOURI. DURING THE FISCAL YEAR, THE ORGANIZATION HAD 9,994 DENTAL ENCOUNTERS (VISITS).

ProgSrvcAccomActy3Grp.Desc: MISSOURI OZARKS COMMUNITY HEALTH PROVIDES QUALITY BEHAVIORAL HEALTH SERVICES TO DOUGLAS, OZARK, WRIGHT, AND TEXAS COUNTIES IN MISSOURI. THESE SERVICES INCLUDE, BUT ARE NOT LIMITED TO, INDIVIDUAL COUNSELING, FAMILY COUNSELING, CONSULTATION, REFERRAL FOR LONG-TERM PSYCHOTHERAPY, MEDICATION EVALUATION, AND SUBSTANCE ABUSE COUNSELING. DURING THE FISCAL YEAR, THE ORGANIZATION HAD 1,179 BEHAVIORAL HEALTH ENCOUNTERS (VISITS).

ORGANIZATION'S MISSION OR MOST SIGNIFICANT ACTIVITIES: THE MISSION OF THE DOUGLAS COUNTY PUBLIC HEALTH SERVICES GROUP, INC.(DCPHSG), DOING BUSINESS AS MISSOURI OZARKS COMMUNITY HEALTH (MOCH), IS, AS A COMMUNITY HEALTH CENTER, TO PROVIDE AFFORDABLE, ACCESSIBLE, QUALITY HEALTH CARE TO ALL WITHIN THE DESIGNATED SERVICE AREA. THESE SERVICES WILL BE PROVIDED WITHOUT REGARD TO AGE, RACE, CREED, DISABILITY OR ECONOMIC STATUS. THESE SERVICES CONSIST OF USUAL AND CUSTOMARY SERVICES AS DEFINED BY THE TERM PRIMARY MEDICAL, MENTAL AND DENTAL HEALTH CARE NEEDS.
VOLUNTEERS: THE ORGANIZATION HAS A VOLUNTEER BOARD OF DIRECTORS.

OTHER PROGRAM SERVICES: MISSOURI OZARKS COMMUNITY HEALTH OPERATES A WELLNESS CENTER THAT SERVES, ON AVERAGE, 950 MEMBERS MONTHLY. THE WELLNESS CENTER PROMOTES HEALTHY LIFESTYLE CHANGES THROUGH EXERCISE AND FITNESS PROGRAMS.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 11B
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: REVIEW OF THE FORM 990: THE FORM 990 IS PREPARED BY AN INDEPENDENT ACCOUNTING FIRM BASED ON THE AUDITED FINANCIAL STATEMENTS AND INFORMATION PROVIDED BY THE ACCOUNTING DEPARTMENT OF THE ORGANIZATION. THE DRAFT FORM 990 IS INITIALLY INTERNALLY REVIEWED IN DETAIL BY THE CEO AND CFO. AFTER ANY REVISIONS ARE MADE BY THE CEO AND CFO, A COPY OF THE 990 IS PROVIDED TO THE FULL BOARD. THE BOARD IS THEN GIVEN AN OPPORTUNITY TO PROVIDE SUGGESTIONS FOR REVISIONS. AFTER ALL REVISIONS ARE COMPLETE, THE FORM 990 IS FILED.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 12C
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: MONITORING COMPLIANCE WITH CONFLICT OF INTEREST POLICY: THE ORGANIZATION HAS A WRITTEN CONFLICT OF INTEREST POLICY. COMPLIANCE WITH THIS POLICY IS REVIEWED AT STAFF MEETINGS AND MONTHLY BOARD MEETINGS, AS THE NEED ARISES. ANY DUALITY OF INTEREST OR POSSIBLE CONFLICT OF INTEREST ON THE PART OF ANY DIRECTOR SHALL BE DISCLOSED TO OTHER MEMBERS OF THE BOARD OF DIRECTORS. TO THIS END, EACH DIRECTOR SHALL UPON ELECTION AND ANNUALLY THEREAFTER, PREPARE AND FILE WITH THE SECRETARY, A WRITTEN DECLARATION OF INTERESTS AND ACTIVITIES WHICH CREATE OR MIGHT CREATE DUAL INTEREST OR CONFLICT OF INTEREST ON THE PART OF THE DIRECTORS. SAID DECLARATIONS SHALL BE AVAILABLE FOR REVIEW BY ALL DIRECTORS AT ALL TIMES. ANY DIRECTOR HAVING A DUALITY OF INTEREST OR POSSIBLE CONFLICT OF INTEREST ON ANY MATTER SHALL NOT VOTE OR USE HIS/HER PERSONAL INFLUENCE ON THE MATTER AND HE/SHE SHALL NOT BE COUNTED IN DETERMINING THE QUORUM FOR THE MEETING. THE MINUTES SHALL REFLECT THE DISCLOSURE, THE ABSTENTION FROM VOTING, AND THE QUORUM STATUS. THE FOREGOING REQUIREMENTS, HOWEVER, SHALL NOT BE CONSTRUED AS PREVENTING THE DIRECTOR FROM STATING HIS/HER POSITION ON THE MATTER NOR FROM ANSWERING PERTINENT QUESTIONS OF OTHER MEMBERS, SINCE HIS/HER KNOWLEDGE MAY BE OF GREAT ASSISTANCE TO THE BOARD.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 15A
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: COMPENSATION REVIEW POLICY: THE BOARD REVIEWS THE CEO'S COMPENSATION ANNUALLY USING THE NACHC SALARY SURVEY AND STATE OF MISSOURI SALARY COMPARABILITY DATA. USING THAT DATA, AND PERFORMANCE EVALUATION, THE WAGE IS ADJUSTED. THE BOARD VOTES ON ANY SALARY ADJUSTMENT, INCLUDING BONUSES, AND THE ACTIONS TAKEN BY THE BOARD ARE DOCUMENTED IN THE BOARD MINUTES. THE CEO PERFORMS ANNUAL REVIEW AS SUPERVISOR FOR ALL OTHER OFFICERS. ALL OTHER COMPENSATION IS DETERMINED BY THE CEO USING GUIDANCE FROM THE STATE OF MISSOURI AND IS BASED ON MERIT. A REVIEW OF THE COMPENSATION OF THE CEO WAS COMPLETED IN 2017.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION C, LINE 19
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: DOCUMENT AVAILABILITY: THE ORGANIZATION'S GOVERNING DOCUMENTS AND CONFLICT OF INTEREST POLICY CAN BE VIEWED AT THE ORGANIZATION'S FACILITY, UPON REQUEST. THE ORGANIZATION'S FINANCIAL STATEMENTS MAY BE AVAILABLE UPON WRITTEN REQUEST IF THE ORGANIZATION DEEMS THE REQUEST FOR VIEWING IS APPROPRIATE. WRITTEN REQUESTS SHOULD INCLUDE WHY THE INTERESTED PARTY REQUESTS TO VIEW THE FINANCIAL STATEMENTS.
